Vice President Biden and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement expressing their sorrow and condolences to the Emanuel AME Church family in Charleston, South Carolina, after a shooting took place there. They remembered Reverend Clementa Pinckney, who was a good man and a man of faith. They also emphasized the need to address gun violence and hatred in the nation. They acknowledged the unity and strength of the Charleston community and pledged their support to the grieving families.